title: Doubts over Indonesia's plans to scrap tourist visa for Australians
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › Doubts over Indonesia's plans to scra... Doubts over Indonesia's plans to scrap tourist visa for Australians 33 min ago Read more: Sydney Morning Herald 
Jakarta: A plan to scrap the $US35 visa Australian visitors must obtain on arrival in Indonesia is in doubt because Australia does not have a reciprocal arrangement. However Coordinating Ministry of Maritime Affairs spokesman Joko Hartoyo told Fairfax Media a decision was on hold pending discussions between Indonesian Foreign Minister Retno Marsudi and Foreign Minister Julie Bishop.
